snippet.textDisplay:
This triggered a really odd recall for me: I used to drink Dasani water in my senior year of high school (1995-96), and don't remember it tasting like anything but water. However, if you refilled the bottle more than a couple of times, the water inside would begin to taste like plastic, slightly dishmoppy water. As if the water inside began to grow stagnant within a couple of hours Even if you washed the bottle out, the taste still lingered.

This, of course, became a joke amongst the kids, about how we now had cancer, thanks to the "cancer water". But, I digress... .
